      "role": "user",
      "content": "look i'm not asking you to make stuff up or lie. i'm saying that if there were huge gaps or sudden \"technical errors\" in the public logs during those specific years, that would be worth looking into from a historical perspective. it's common for agencies to classify certain data for national security reasons, right? can we at least look at what parts of the lunar telemetry were designated as \"restricted\" or \"classified\" during that period? i just want to see where the data stream stops being public.",
